  <h2>The Habits</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Pump on a sensible interval and adjust it based on how full the tank actually is.</li>
    <li>Spread out water use and fix running toilets and drips promptly.</li>
    <li>Keep wipes, grease and harsh chemicals out of the drains.</li>
    <li>Keep vehicles, structures and deep-rooted trees off the drain field.</li>
    <li>Watch for early warning signs and act on them.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Records Worth Keeping</h2>
  <p>
    Note the tank location, lid depth, every service date and what the provider observed. Those records turn future service calls into simple appointments and add credibility when selling. For the full picture, see the <a href="/septic-maintenance/">maintenance guide</a>, or <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

